The '''2012 Astrakhan gas explosion''' occurred on February 27, 2012 at an apartment building in the city of [[Astrakhan]], [[Astrakhan Oblast]], [[Russia]]. It was caused by a natural gas explosion. The blast killed at least 10 people and injured 12.<ref>http://rt.com/news/russia-building-collapse-victims-363/</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Leon Watson |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2107318/Two-dead-11-missing-blast-rips-old-Soviet-style-block-Russia.html |title=Two dead and 11 missing after blast rips through old Soviet-style block in Russia &#124; Mail Online |publisher=Dailymail.co.uk |date=2012-02-24 |accessdate=2012-02-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/video/2012/02/28/deadly-building-collapse-in-russia?videoId=230908471&videoChannel=117760 |title=Deadly building collapse in Russia &#124; Video |publisher=Reuters.com |date=2009-02-09 |accessdate=2012-02-28}}</ref>
==Explosion== A nine-storey apartment block collapsed after a gas explosion. The rescuers battled to find up to 14 people still feared trapped under the rubble.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.englishrussia.com/2012/02/27/9-storey-building-collapses-in-astrakhan/ |title=9-Storey Building Collapses In Astrakhan |publisher=English Russia |date= |accessdate=2012-02-28}}</ref>
