'''Einar Bakke Håndlykken''' (born August 9, 1976 in [[Trondheim]], [[Norway]]) is a Norwegian [[environmentalism|environmentalist]] and director of [[Zero Emission Resource Organisation]] (ZERO).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hydro.com/en/Press-room/News/Archive/2011/April/Norways-first-energy-positive-office-building/|title=Norway’s first energy-positive office building |accessdate=5 June 2011}}</ref> Håndlykken started with environmentalism as a youth in [[Grenland]] [[Natur og Ungdom]], and became deputy chairman of the national organisation in 1997 and in 1999 and 2000 he was chairman. He worked for [[Bellona Foundation|Bellona]] from 2001 to 2002, when he co-founded ZERO.

