'''Tricosylic acid''', or ''tricosanoic acid'', is a 23-[[carbon]] long-chain [[saturated fatty acid]] with the [[chemical formula]] CH<sub>3</sub>(CH<sub>2</sub>)<sub>21</sub>COOH.
