The '''xenonium ion''', XeH<sup>+</sup>, is an [[onium compound]], consisting of [[Protonation|protonated]] [[xenon]].  Although the existence of the xenonium [[cation]] itself has not been proven, [[Salt (chemistry)|salts]] of the fluoroxenonium ion, XeF<sup>+</sup>, are known to exist, for instance fluoroxenonium pentafluoroplatinate (XeFPtF<sub>5</sub>), more commonly known as [[xenon hexafluoroplatinate]].<ref>Holleman, A. F.; Wiberg, E. "Inorganic Chemistry" Academic Press: San Diego, 2001. {{ISBN|0-12-352651-5}}.</ref>

